.TH MULTIFLEXI\-SCHEDULER 8 "June 2026" "multiflexi-scheduler 2.2.0" "MultiFlexi"
.SH NAME
multiflexi\-scheduler \- schedule MultiFlexi jobs by interval
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B multiflexi\-scheduler
.I INTERVAL
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B multiflexi\-scheduler
queries the MultiFlexi database for all active RunTemplates whose interval
matches
.I INTERVAL
and enqueues a job for each of them.
It is intended to be called from a cron job or a systemd timer once per
interval period.
.PP
For continuous, cron-expression-based scheduling see the
.B multiflexi\-scheduler\-daemon
systemd service, which runs
.B daemon.php
in the background and handles custom cron expressions natively.
.SH INTERVALS
.TP
.B i
Every minute
.TP
.B h
Every hour
.TP
.B d
Every day
.TP
.B w
Every week
.TP
.B m
Every month
.TP
.B y
Every year
.SH OPTIONS
No additional options are supported.
The interval character is the sole positional argument.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Configuration is read from
.I /etc/multiflexi/multiflexi.env
(or a
.I .env
file one level above the script).
.TP
.B DB_CONNECTION
Database driver:
.BR mysql ", " pgsql ", " sqlite " (default: mysql)"
.TP
.B DB_HOST
Database host (default:
.BR localhost )
.TP
.B DB_PORT
Database port
.TP
.B DB_DATABASE
Database name
.TP
.B DB_USERNAME
Database user
.TP
.B DB_PASSWORD
Database password
.TP
.B APP_DEBUG
Set to
.B true
to enable verbose console logging.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Interval argument missing or no matching RunTemplates found.
.TP
.B 1
Interval argument missing (usage error).
.SH DAEMON
The long-running daemon variant is managed by systemd:
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl start multiflexi-scheduler
systemctl enable multiflexi-scheduler
.fi
.RE
.PP
The daemon acquires an exclusive lock on
.I $TMPDIR/multiflexi-scheduler.pid
at startup.
If a second instance is launched while the first is running it exits
immediately, preventing the same RunTemplate from being scheduled twice.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/multiflexi/multiflexi.env
Runtime environment configuration.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/multiflexi-scheduler/daemon.php
Continuous scheduling daemon (custom cron expressions).
.TP
.I /usr/lib/multiflexi-scheduler/scheduler.php
One-shot interval scheduler called by this binary.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR multiflexi-executor (8)
